The Caretaker and Extra-ordinary Convention Planning Committee (CECPC) yesterday appointed Zonal Congress Election Sub-committees for each of the six geo-political zones ahead of the March 12 Congresses. A statement in Abuja by its secretary, Senator John James Akpanudoedehe, said each of the zonal committees is being headed by a member of the Caretaker Committee   Tinubu visits Ooni, Owa Obokun, gets blessings     Al-Makura, two others reject APC’s zoning, consensus plans     El-Rufai: resources in terrorists’ hands can subvert Nigeria   He said: “The chairmen of the committees are all members of the CECPC, while secretaries are selected from among the deputy governors from their respective geo-political zones. “Meetings of zonal stakeholders holds on Saturday, Feb. 26, at the respective geo-political zones.” The committee chairmen are Governor Abubakar Sani Bello (Northcentral); Prof. Tahoe Mamman (SAN) (Northeast) committee Senator Abba Ali (Northwest), former Senate President  Ken Nnamani (Southeast); former Bayelsa State governorship candidate, David Lyon (Southsouth) and Akinremi Olaide (Southwest).